Description:
Design Excellence For Outstanding Family Living
Exceptional in its use of space, light and high-end finishes this modern three bedroom two bathroom residence promises an outstanding family lifestyle moments to parks, McNamara Avenue shops and leading schools. As new and showcasing coveted contemporary design this sleek home with a wide entrance hall and plush carpets in a versatile theatre room hits a highpoint with its expansive open plan living. A sublime custom CaesarStone waterfall island kitchen boasting a full suite of Bosch appliances takes centre stage in this living space that opens to an elevated deck and gardens, with direct access to the Green Spine walking track, to create a stylish entertainers haven. Add three spacious bedrooms, luxe bathrooms, master with ensuite, WIR and balcony, heating/cooling, fully cabled network and integrated audio, alarm, and garage with remote and internal access plus off-street parking, moments to Keilor Road, Westfield and Essendon Fields shopping precincts, inspection will impress.

Description:
Renovated single level entertainer.
A pleasure for entertaining inside and out, this beautifully renovated three bedroom residence features a private all-weather alfresco entertaining zone, with gas-to-mains barbeque, set amidst idyllic landscaped gardens. Offering flexibility and flair, an immaculate layout comprises an inviting entry hall flowing to stylish living/dining zones and family/study area enjoying a lovely garden outlook. A modern stone and Miele kitchen is a classy hub enhanced by quality stainless steel appliances, dishwasher, plentiful soft-close cabinetry and stone benches, including breakfast nook. Elegantly serving three robed bedrooms are pristine bathroom, flaunting spa bath, second bathroom with shower, vanity and separate toilet. Complemented by split-system air conditioners, ducted heating, ceiling fans, polished Tassie Oak floorboards, solar electricity, storage, garden shed and double carport. Walking distance to St Peters Primary, Milleara Shopping Centre, parklands, buses and freeways.

Description:
Luxurious & Low Maintenance
This neat and tidy two-bedroom property is certain to attract downsizers, first homebuyers or an investor looking to get a foothold into this popular suburb. Set at the end of a quiet cul-de-sac on its own title and free from Body Corporate, the home provides a low maintenance aspect. The large lounge provides an abundance of space and natural light, while the updated bathroom with double vanity services the two bedrooms. A renovated kitchen complete with stone benches and stainless steel appliances adjoins the meals area, leading out to the courtyard and generous backyard with gate access, ideal for a car, trailer or boat accommodation. Extras include built-in-robes, reverse cycle air conditioning, heating and lock-up single car garage. Currently leased until June 2020 and returning $1,673pcm, it is within close proximity to Centreway Shopping precinct, buses, and schools including Penleigh and Essendon Grammar and freeway access.

Description:
Beyond the Picturesque Facade.
Stunning from the outside this near new four bedroom three bathroom, townhouse is big on space and features three great living areas. With nothing to do but move in, a timeless and consistent colour palette endures throughout this light filled home. The fully equipped kitchen features a suite of stainless steel appliances, stone benchtops and central island with breakfast bar and pendant lighting all highlighted further by mirrored splashbacks. The dining and living space can be mixed and matched accordingly and accesses the undercover alfresco entertaining area and freshly landscaped garden via large glass sliders. Two master bedrooms feature walk in robes and ensuites, while the remaining two bedrooms have walk in robes. Pristine bathrooms feature floor to ceiling tiling, raised vanities, stone benchtops and soft close cabinetry. Remote integrated garage, alarm, heating, cooling, storage facilities and schools, transport and all amenities close by.

Description:
Location, Luxury and Sensational New Style!
Set at the rear in a boutique new block of six, this townhouse sensation delivers an executive lifestyle of low-maintenance perfection with its architectural excellence, first-class features throughout and enviable heart-of-Niddrie convenience. Intelligently designed to maximise light and space, the home's on-trend interior boasts three generous bedrooms (large master) all with built-in robes, deluxe ensuite and equally-stylish main bathroom - both with stone-top vanities, recessed cisterns and floor-to-ceiling tiles. Adaptable to your individual requirements, the versatile open-plan living/dining area is accompanied by a superb stone-bench kitchen complete with Smeg appliances and ample cupboard space. Ducted heating and refrigerated cooling add to the appeal, along with high square-set ceilings throughout, alarm and video intercom, laundry and third WC, premium fittings and flooring, soft-close cabinetry and double-glazed windows. Making the most of its rear position, the home also includes a surprisingly large full-width rear courtyard with high fences all-round for added peace of mind, plus the added advantage of a remote-control double garage with internal entry. A short stroll to Keilor Road trams and cosmopolitan shopping precinct, the area's cool cafes and renowned restaurants, it's also close to a range of primary and secondary schools as well as easy freeway access.

Description:
Extraordinary Indoor / Outdoor Family Entertainer
Surrounded by lush landscaped gardens on a substantial block of land (approx 650sqm), this single-level showpiece has been custom-designed for those that love to entertain with its expanded floorplan, versatile living zones and private resort-style backyard. Bold and beautiful, the home's opulent interior comprises three genuinely large bedrooms (all with mirrored robes), master ensuite with spa, main family bathroom and separate powder room. Adding to its appeal is modern stone-top kitchen with soft-close cabinetry and European appliances, expansive open-plan lounge/dining area leading through to a separate living area complete with wet-bar and integrated entertainment cabinetry, plus a simply spectacular al-fresco deck with BBQ kitchen, integrated audio and mesh cafe blinds. Along with ducted heating and evaporative cooling, the home also includes a gas-log fireplace (lounge area), alarm and video intercom, solid hardwood floors, large laundry and excellent storage options throughout. Completing the picture is a private backyard garden with extensive paving and fully-tiled solar-heated pool, plus under-house storage, 5000L watertank and tandem double garage via gated side driveway (both r/c). Close to Keilor Road trams, shops and renowned eateries, the area's renowned primary and secondary schools, Steele Creek trails and parkland as well as easy access to Melbourne Airport and CBD via freeway/Citylink. Land approx. 15.3m x 42.5m (650m2).

Description:
Stand out from the crowd.
Testament to both cutting edge design and building expertise, these brand new, architecturally designed three bedroom, two bathroom townhouses are simply stunning. Revealed behind their striking facades are opulent open plan living, dining spaces featuring high ceilings, premium hardwood floors and vast glass aspects spilling to north facing alfresco decks and private courtyards. Adorned with Versilia Grey marble bench tops, stainless steel Ariston appliances and premium cabinetry, the kitchens are all class. Both properties offer three robed bedrooms, including master suites flaunting Bianco Carrara marble ensuite with Nero tapware and rainfall showers. Further highlights include deluxe marble bathrooms, powder rooms, laundries, storage, integrated refrigerated heating/cooling systems, split-system air conditioners, automated garages with epoxy flake flooring. Close to Keilor Road precinct, La Manna, private and public schools, No. 59 tram and freeways.

In a popular location just moments from primary schools, Brimbank Shopping Centre, parks and bus services.
